<task id="AIPU2-025" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build ConfidenceScoringService — Per-Response Confidence Levels</title>
    <phase>2B</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai-safety</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-021</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Build ConfidenceScoringService that produces a calibrated confidence level (High / Medium / Low) for
    each AI response based on the number and quality of source passages that support the response. The score
    is derived from the groundedness check results (how many segments are grounded) and the RAG retrieval
    quality (how many source passages were available). The confidence level is emitted as part of the
    safety_annotation SSE event so the UI can display a confidence indicator alongside the AI response.
    See spec.md FR-406 for the full requirements.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET backend engineer with Spaarke AI safety pipeline experience.</role>
  <goal>
    ConfidenceScoringService returns High, Medium, or Low for each response, calibrated to source passage
    count and groundedness ratio. Confidence level is included in the safety_annotation SSE event.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r2/spec.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read spec.md FR-406 for the confidence scoring thresholds and calibration rules.</step>
    <step>Create ConfidenceLevel.cs enum: High, Medium, Low.</step>
    <step>Create ConfidenceScoringRequest.cs record: SourcePassageCount (int), GroundednessResult (GroundednessResult — from task 021), ResponseLength (int — character count of LLM response), CitationCount (int — citations extracted by CitationExtractor).</step>
    <step>Create ConfidenceScoringResult.cs record: Level (ConfidenceLevel), Score (float 0-1), Rationale (string — human-readable explanation of why this level was assigned).</step>
    <step>Create IConfidenceScoringService.cs interface with: ConfidenceScoringResult Score(ConfidenceScoringRequest request).</step>
    <step>Create ConfidenceScoringService.cs implementing IConfidenceScoringService (synchronous — no I/O, pure computation). Implement scoring logic:
      - Compute groundedness_ratio = (total_segments - ungrounded_count) / max(total_segments, 1)
      - Compute source_score = min(SourcePassageCount / 5.0, 1.0) (5+ passages = max source score)
      - Compute raw_score = (groundedness_ratio * 0.6) + (source_score * 0.4)
      - Map: raw_score >= 0.75 → High, 0.40-0.74 → Medium, &lt; 0.40 → Low
      - Override to Low when SourcePassageCount == 0 regardless of other scores
      - Build Rationale string summarizing the inputs and decision.</step>
    <step>Integrate into the safety_annotation SSE event: extend the groundedness event payload (from task 021) to include a confidence field: { "type": "groundedness", "isGrounded": bool, "ungroundedSegments": [...], "confidence": { "level": "High|Medium|Low", "score": float, "rationale": string } }. Alternatively emit as a separate safety_annotation sub-event if the existing structure is already emitted separately — follow the established pattern.</step>
    <step>Register IConfidenceScoringService as a singleton in AddAiSafetyModule().</step>
    <step>Write unit tests covering all three levels: 5 sources + fully grounded → High, 2 sources + partially grounded → Medium, 0 sources → Low override, 5 sources + 50% ungrounded → Medium.</step>
    <step>Run `dotnet build` and `dotnet test --filter "ConfidenceScor"` to verify.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>ConfidenceLevel.High returned when source_passage_count &gt;= 5 and groundedness_ratio &gt;= 0.75.</criterion>
    <criterion>ConfidenceLevel.Low always returned when source_passage_count == 0.</criterion>
    <criterion>ConfidenceLevel.Medium returned for the middle band (0.40-0.74 raw score).</criterion>
    <criterion>Rationale string is non-empty and describes the inputs that drove the decision.</criterion>
    <criterion>Confidence level included in the safety_annotation SSE event payload.</criterion>
    <criterion>Service is synchronous (no async) — no I/O, pure computation.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests pass: `dotnet test --filter "ConfidenceScor"`.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
